This paper is likely to belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category as it proposes a method to overcome the problem of local optima in Genetic Algorithm by controlling the diversity of the population. It also involves a self-adaptation mechanism that can adapt the population towards proper diversity for the problems. Additionally, it may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories as it involves optimization techniques and learning algorithms. The System and Control (cs.SY) sub-category may also be relevant as it deals with the control of the population diversity. Finally, the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category may be relevant as it involves the optimization of candidate solutions.
